# On-Train Food Ordering & Feedback System - Walkthrough

## What Was Accomplished
We successfully built a modern, premium Next.js application that solves the problem of unpredictable food quality and delivery timing on trains. The app features a stunning UI built with Tailwind CSS, Framer Motion for animations, and Lucide React for iconography.

### Key Features Implemented:
1. **Premium Landing Page**: An animated, high-quality dark mode landing page allowing users to track their PNR or begin an order.
2. **AI-Driven Menu (Mocked)**: The `/order` page displays mock food items with an AI recommendation section that filters food based on preferences and context.
3. **Dynamic Prep & "Hold/Pivot" Logic**: The system tracks the dynamic position of the train (mocked via [lib/mockNTES.ts](file:///c:/Users/SREYA%20DATTA%20GUPTA/Desktop/xfdghj/lib/mockNTES.ts)) and only signals the kitchen to start preparing food when the train is within an optimal distance (e.g., `< 50km`) of the station.
4. **Visual Delivery Map**: We integrated React-Leaflet to show a stunning dark-themed live map of the train approaching the station and the delivery agent waiting on the platform.
5. **Secure Escrow Payment**: Funds are "Locked" in escrow upon ordering. Only when the customer shares the secure OTP with the delivery agent on the platform are the funds "Released" to the kitchen vendor.

## What Was Tested
- **Routing & Components**: All Next.js routes (`/`, `/order`, `/tracker`) render successfully without layout shifts.
- **Dynamic Train Position**: The mock NTES poll loop (every 3 seconds) correctly updates the train speed, coordinates, and ETA in the `/tracker` route.
- **Map Bounds Adjustments**: The React-Leaflet map automatically adjusts its bounds to keep the Train, Agent, and Vendor within view as the train coordinates update.
- **Escrow Verification**: Submitting the correct `DEMO_OTP` (123456) successfully releases the funds and updates the UI status.

## How to Verify Locally
Since the environment execution policy restricts running scripts on the current shell, you can start the development server manually.

1. Open your terminal in the project directory: `c:/Users/SREYA DATTA GUPTA/Desktop/xfdghj`.
2. Run `npm run dev`.
3. Navigate to `http://localhost:3000`.
4. Click **Order Now** to add items to the cart and proceed.
5. On the **Tracker** page, watch the dynamic progress bar as the train distance reaches the stop mark, triggering the kitchen preparation and delivery agent dispatch. Enter `123456` when prompted for the OTP!

## Automated Browser Testing
The AI browser subagent successfully ran an end-to-end test of the entire application flow in the browser. 
It navigated from the landing page, added AI-recommended food to the cart, watched the live tracker and map as the mocked train moved, and successfully verified the mock escrow OTP to release funds when the agent reached the platform.

